SUMMARY:Board Game Night: For Members & Guests Only!
DESCRIPTION:MAKE Roanoke\nJoin us for a fun-filled evening of board games and camaraderie at MAKE Roanoke! Whether you're a seasoned strategist or a casual player\, this night welcomes everyone to play\, learn\, and connect with the local maker community.\n\nThis event is free for MAKE Roanoke members and guests of members to attend. A variety of board games will be provided by our hosts\, and attendees are welcome to bring their favorite games. [Find out more about MAKE Roanoke Membership here.](https://www.makeroanoke.org/become-a-member)\n\nMembers are responsible for their guests at all times\, and must ensure they sign-in and complete a waiver on entry.\n\n**Please note that MAKE Roanoke is an active workshop:**\n\n* All participants must have a signed waiver on file. If the participant is a minor\, the waiver must be signed by a parent or court-appointed legal guardian. Waivers can be filled out ahead of time at [https://mkroa.org/waiver](https://mkroa.org/waiver "https://mkroa.org/waiver")\n* Children who are not participating in the event are not permitted in the space.\n* Closed toed shoes are required in the space at all times by everyone\, regardless of age or participation in an event. No sandals\, crocs\, or bare feet.\n* You may be asked to remove or tuck in dangling jewelry\, lanyards\, etc for safety.\n* Depending on the activity\, other dress code rules may apply.
